<section class="product-desc-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="product-desc-grid">
      <div class="product-desc">
        <div class="section-tag">Product Overview</div>
        <div class="divider"></div>
        <h2>Precision-Milled for <span>Advanced</span> Applications</h2>
        <p>Our milled sepiolite powder is produced through a controlled grinding and classification process that reduces raw ore to ultra-fine particles while preserving the mineral's unique fibrous nanostructure. This structure is key to its exceptional rheological and adsorptive properties.</p>
        <p>Available in multiple grades from 5 to 200 microns, the powder exhibits remarkably high specific surface area (200–300 m²/g) that provides outstanding thixotropic behavior in liquid systems. This makes it indispensable as a rheology modifier in paints, coatings, and adhesives.</p>
        <p>In pharmaceutical and cosmetic applications, milled sepiolite serves as an excipient, carrier, and stabilizer. Its natural origin, chemical inertness, and high purity make it suitable for sensitive formulations where synthetic alternatives are undesirable.</p>
        <p>Our milling facility operates with precision air classifiers that ensure tight particle size distribution. D50 and D90 values are verified on every batch, giving formulators the consistency they need for reproducible end products.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="tech-specs-card">
          <h3>
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><path d="M10 2L18 7V13L10 18L2 13V7L10 2Z" stroke="#C9922A" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/><circle cx="10" cy="10" r="3" fill="#C9922A"/></svg>
            Technical Specifications
          </h3>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">Product Form</span>
            <span class="spec-value">Fine Powder</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">Particle Size Range</span>
            <span class="spec-value">5–200 μm</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">D50 (typical)</span>
            <span class="spec-value">15–45 μm</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">Specific Surface Area</span>
            <span class="spec-value">200–300 m²/g</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">MgO</span>
            <span class="spec-value">≥ 18%</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">SiO₂</span>
            <span class="spec-value">≥ 54%</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">Moisture</span>
            <span class="spec-value">≤ 10%</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">pH (10% suspension)</span>
            <span class="spec-value">8.0–9.5</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">Color</span>
            <span class="spec-value">White</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">Oil Absorption</span>
            <span class="spec-value">120–180 g/100g</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">Packaging</span>
            <span class="spec-value">25kg Bags / 1 MT Bags</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">Delivery</span>
            <span class="spec-value">FOB Mersin / Samsun</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="usage-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="usage-header">
      <div class="section-tag" style="color:var(--gold-light);">Applications</div>
      <div class="divider divider--center"></div>
      <h2 class="section-title" style="color:var(--white);">Where Milled Sepiolite Powder <span>Is Used</span></h2>
    </div>
    <div class="usage-grid">
      <div class="usage-card reveal">
        <div class="usage-icon">🎨</div>
        <h3>Paints & Coatings</h3>
        <p>Provides thixotropic behavior and anti-settling properties in water-based and solvent-based formulations. Prevents pigment sedimentation while maintaining easy brushability and spray application.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="usage-card reveal">
        <div class="usage-icon">💊</div>
        <h3>Pharmaceuticals</h3>
        <p>Used as an excipient, controlled-release carrier, and stabilizer in tablet and suspension formulations. Natural origin and chemical inertness meet pharmaceutical-grade requirements.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="usage-card reveal">
        <div class="usage-icon">🧴</div>
        <h3>Cosmetics & Personal Care</h3>
        <p>Serves as a natural thickener, oil absorber, and texture enhancer in creams, lotions, masks, and powder foundations. Gentle on skin with no irritation profile.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="usage-card reveal">
        <div class="usage-icon">🏺</div>
        <h3>Ceramics & Refractories</h3>
        <p>Incorporated into ceramic bodies and glazes to improve green strength, reduce shrinkage, and enhance thermal shock resistance in kiln-fired products.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="usage-card reveal">
        <div class="usage-icon">🧪</div>
        <h3>Adhesives & Sealants</h3>
        <p>Acts as a thixotropic agent in construction adhesives, tile mortars, and industrial sealants. Prevents sagging on vertical surfaces while maintaining workability.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="usage-card reveal">
        <div class="usage-icon">🖌️</div>
        <h3>Plastics & Polymers</h3>
        <p>Used as a reinforcing filler in thermoplastics and thermosets. Improves dimensional stability, reduces warping, and can enhance flame retardancy in compound formulations.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="advantages-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="advantages-grid">
      <div>
        <div class="section-tag">Why Choose Us</div>
        <div class="divider"></div>
        <h2 class="section-title">Key <span>Advantages</span></h2>
        <div class="advantage-list">
          <div class="advantage-item reveal">
            <div class="advantage-num">01</div>
            <div>
              <strong>Controlled Particle Distribution</strong>
              <p>Precision air classification ensures tight D50 and D90 values batch after batch, critical for reproducible formulations in paints and pharma.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="advantage-item reveal">
            <div class="advantage-num">02</div>
            <div>
              <strong>Exceptional Surface Area</strong>
              <p>At 200–300 m²/g, our milled powder offers one of the highest surface areas among natural minerals — essential for rheology modification.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="advantage-item reveal">
            <div class="advantage-num">03</div>
            <div>
              <strong>Chemical Inertness</strong>
              <p>Sepiolite powder is chemically stable across pH 3–11, compatible with most formulation systems, and does not react with active ingredients.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="advantage-item reveal">
            <div class="advantage-num">04</div>
            <div>
              <strong>Natural & Sustainable</strong>
              <p>A naturally occurring mineral requiring no chemical synthesis — meeting growing demand for clean-label and green-chemistry ingredients.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="advantage-item reveal">
            <div class="advantage-num">05</div>
            <div>
              <strong>Versatile Particle Grades</strong>
              <p>From 5μm ultra-fine for pharma to 200μm coarse for construction — we produce the exact grade your application demands.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="advantage-image">
        <img width="787" height="1050" src="/images/factory/factory-interior-03.webp" alt="Sepiolite mine – Zamana Turkey" loading="lazy" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="faq-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="faq-header">
      <div class="section-tag">Common Questions</div>
      <div class="divider divider--center"></div>
      <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked <span>Questions</span></h2>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          What particle sizes are available for milled sepiolite?
          <svg class="faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><path d="M5 7.5L10 12.5L15 7.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">
          We offer grades ranging from 5 to 200 microns. Standard grades include ultra-fine (D50: 15μm), fine (D50: 25μm), medium (D50: 45μm), and coarse (D50: 100μm+). Custom milling is available.
        </div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          Is milled sepiolite suitable for food-contact applications?
          <svg class="faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><path d="M5 7.5L10 12.5L15 7.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">
          Sepiolite is approved for food-contact use in many jurisdictions. We can provide specific compliance documentation upon request for your target market.
        </div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          How does sepiolite powder compare to fumed silica as a thickener?
          <svg class="faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><path d="M5 7.5L10 12.5L15 7.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">
          Sepiolite provides similar thixotropic performance at lower cost. It offers better suspension of heavy pigments and is easier to disperse without specialized equipment.
        </div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          What is the shelf life of milled sepiolite powder?
          <svg class="faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><path d="M5 7.5L10 12.5L15 7.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">
          When stored in sealed packaging in dry conditions, milled sepiolite has an indefinite shelf life. The mineral is chemically stable and does not degrade over time.
        </div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          Can you provide samples for formulation testing?
          <svg class="faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><path d="M5 7.5L10 12.5L15 7.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">
          Yes, we supply 1–5 kg samples of all powder grades with full technical data sheets. Contact our sales team to specify your required particle size.
        </div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="related-section">
